SMTP - Simple Mail Transfer Protocol. It is a protocol used ONLY to send emails to server (to download use IMAP or POP3).
      A message can have one or more receipients and one sender. So when You send an email it goes to SMTP server and
      this server sends it to receipients SMTP servers and then they can be downloaded using IMAP or POP3.
      
      CLIENT_1   ---SMTP-->   SMTP_SERVER_1   ---SMTP-->   SMTP_SERVER_2   <--IMAP/POP3---   CLIENT_2
      
SMTP REPLY CODES:
...
220	- <domain> Service ready
250 - Requested mail action okay, completed
...
https://www.greenend.org.uk/rjk/tech/smtpreplies.html
